<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1418] MarkupBuilder does not escape element content correctly if it contains EOL sequences</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1418</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MarkupBuilder does not correctly escape element content that contains end of line characters/sequences. For example, the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def b = new MarkupBuilder()&lt;br/&gt;
b.element(&quot;&quot;&quot;test&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;&quot;&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;will generate XML that looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;element&amp;gt;test&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/element&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that the &quot;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&quot; sequence in the XML should be &quot;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
